# Dashboard Widget Architecture

Home screen (`app/(tabs)/index.tsx`) is a thin shell: header, global filters, customize button, pull-to-refresh. All blocks are composable widgets.

## Adding a new widget

1. Add `WidgetId` to `lib/dashboard/types.ts` (`WIDGET_IDS` array).
2. Register metadata in `lib/dashboard/registry.ts`:
   - `title`, `description`, `tier` (`free` | `pro`), `defaultEnabled`, `defaultOrder`
   - `queryKeys(ctx)` — React Query keys this widget owns (used by central refresh)
   - `usesFilters` if it reads sport/era/priceTier from `DashboardProvider`
3. Create `components/dashboard/widgets/MyWidget.tsx` — self-contained UI + data (`useQuery` inside).
4. Map id → component in `components/dashboard/widget-components.ts`.
5. Wrap with `WidgetErrorBoundary` automatically via `DashboardShell`.

## Rules

- **Widgets own their data.** Never pre-fetch in `index.tsx` and pass down computed props (old `hottestBySport` pattern).
- **Shared filters** come from `useDashboardContext()` — not props from the screen.
- **Shared trending** for filter-aware widgets: `useFilteredTrending()` (React Query dedupes by key).
- **Central refresh**: `useDashboardRefresh(enabledWidgetIds)` invalidates union of registry `queryKeys`. Pull-to-refresh on home uses this.
- **Layout persistence**: `user_dashboard_layout` Supabase table (`widget_order text[]`). Hook: `useDashboardLayout()`.
- **Pro gating**: set `tier: "pro"` in registry; `DashboardShell` renders `WidgetLockedPlaceholder` for free users.
- **Styling**: inline `style={{}}` from `lib/theme.ts` — match existing widgets.

## Key files

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `lib/dashboard/registry.ts` | Widget catalog + query key map |
| `lib/dashboard/dashboard-context.tsx` | Global filters + plan |
| `lib/dashboard/use-dashboard-layout.ts` | Enable/order/reorder + Supabase save |
| `lib/dashboard/use-dashboard-refresh.ts` | Invalidate enabled widget queries |
| `components/dashboard/DashboardShell.tsx` | Renders ordered widgets |
| `components/dashboard/CustomizeDashboardModal.tsx` | Add/remove/reorder UI |

## Decision log

- **2026-06-23** — Widget registry + Supabase layout chosen over local-only. All current widgets are `free`; tier field ready for monetization.
